# Changelog

## 3.3.1 (2026-04-13)

### Out-of-the-Box Experience — Zero Config Required:
- **Default hotkeys registered on first launch**: All six global shortcuts are now active immediately after installation — no manual setup needed. Defaults: `Ctrl+Alt+Q` (Selection Translate), `Ctrl+Alt+W` (Input Translate), `Ctrl+Alt+R` (OCR Recognize), `Ctrl+Alt+O` (OCR Translate), `Ctrl+Alt+M` (Realtime Translate), `Ctrl+Alt+V` (Voice Anywhere). Fully reassignable or clearable in Settings → Hotkey.
- **Service providers pre-seeded on fresh install**: Translate, TTS, Transcription, and AI service lists now populate with sensible defaults on first run rather than showing an empty list. Translate: Transkit Cloud + Google + Bing. TTS: Transkit Cloud + Google TTS + Edge TTS. Transcription: Transkit Cloud STT + Deepgram. AI: Transkit Cloud AI. Free providers (Google, Bing, Edge TTS) work immediately without any API key.
- **Consistent defaults across all windows**: Fixed a race condition where the Translate window, Voice Anywhere, and Config pages each used different default values for the same service list keys — whichever rendered first would win and under-populate the list. All entry points now share the same defaults.

### Reset to Defaults — Settings → About:
- **New "Reset" button** in the System section of the About page.
- **Two-option confirmation modal**:
  - *Reset — Keep API Keys*: Wipes all app settings and resets to factory defaults while preserving every service credential (API keys, auth tokens, custom service configs). Service instance configs stored as `key@id` pairs or plain objects are retained automatically.
  - *Reset Everything*: Clears the entire config store, returning the app to a completely fresh state.
- App restarts automatically after reset; default hotkeys and service lists are re-applied on first launch.

## 3.3.0 (2026-04-13)

### ONNX STT Engine — Windows Support:
- **Windows PATH fix**: The ONNX engine process now inherits the correct Windows system `PATH` instead of overriding it with macOS/Linux paths, allowing Python and native sherpa-onnx DLLs to load correctly.
- **Hidden console window**: Added `CREATE_NO_WINDOW` flag on Windows so no terminal flashes when the ONNX server starts.
- **Windows bundle path**: Added the correct resource path (`scripts/local_sidecar/server.py` next to the `.exe`) for production Windows builds.
- **Crash diagnostics**: Python stderr is now captured and forwarded to the UI via the `onnx-engine://stopped` event so users see the actual error message when the server fails to start.
- **UI error banner**: Start failures (invoke error or process crash) now display a red error banner below the Start/Stop buttons instead of silently logging to console.

## 3.2.9 (2026-04-13)

### Voice Anywhere — Tray & Config Improvements:
- **Favorite Target Languages**: New "Favorite Targets (Tray)" section in Voice Input settings. Configure a personal list of target languages; they appear instantly in the system tray for one-click switching without opening settings.
- **Tray: Translate to (replaces Language)**: The system tray Voice Anywhere submenu now shows a **"Translate to"** section (No translate + favorites) instead of the rarely-changed source language selector — putting the most-used action one click away.
- **Tray Event Sync**: Changing the target language from the tray now emits `voice_anywhere_target_language_changed` so the Config window reflects the selection immediately without a restart.

### Tray Reliability & i18n:
- **Full Tray i18n for Voice Anywhere**: All 12 tray submenu labels (STT Provider, Inherit from Monitor, Translate to, No translate, After Stop, Copy/Paste, Inject Mode, Replace, Append, Configure…) are now localised in all 12 supported tray languages (VI, ZH-CN, ZH-TW, JA, KO, FR, DE, RU, PT-BR, FA, UK, EN).
- **Error-safe tray handlers**: Replaced all `.unwrap()` panics in tray event handlers and `update_tray()` with `warn!`-logged error paths — `set_menu`, `set_tooltip`, all `emit_all` calls, `unregister_all`, and `open log dir` no longer crash the app on failure.

### i18n — 22 Locales:
- Added `common.add`, `config.voice_input.fav_targets`, and `config.voice_input.fav_targets_desc` to all 22 locale files with native translations.

### Documentation — Keyboard Shortcuts:
- Added a **Keyboard Shortcuts** section to all 4 READMEs (EN / VI / CN / KR) documenting the branded `Ctrl+Alt+` hotkey set and explaining cross-platform compatibility (`Ctrl+Alt` = `Ctrl+Option` on macOS, works with one registration across all OS).
- Recommended defaults: `Ctrl+Alt+V` (Voice Anywhere), `Ctrl+Alt+M` (Realtime Translate), `Ctrl+Alt+Q` (Selection Translate), `Ctrl+Alt+W` (Input Translate), `Ctrl+Alt+R` (OCR Recognize), `Ctrl+Alt+O` (OCR Translate).

## 3.2.7 (2026-04-11)
 
### ONNX STT Engine & Models:
- **Enhanced Model Detection**: Fixed logic to correctly identify and load various Zipformer model structures (standard ONNX vs shared sidecar weights).
- **Improved Downloader**: Refined HuggingFace model downloading with better error handling and progress reporting.
- **Engine Reliability**: Optimized the local sidecar engine for more stable WebSocket connections and faster initialization.
 
### UI & Refinement:
- **Config UI Modernization**: Refactored the ONNX STT configuration page with a premium vertical layout using NextUI components, consistent with the app's design system.
- **Standardized Inputs**: Improved usability of STT provider settings with better label placement and aligned action buttons.
 
 
## 3.2.6 (2026-04-10)
 
### Voice Anywhere & Dictation:
- **Native Audio Feedback**: Restored start/stop recording sounds by bypassing browser restrictions using native Rust audio playback. Includes a new toggle in settings to enable/disable sound effects and increased volume for better noticeability.
- **Integrated Translation**: Added **Target Language** support to Voice Anywhere. Speak in one language and have the app instantly translate and inject/pasted the result into any application.
- **AI-Powered Polishing**: New "Polish" mode that uses AI to refine your dictated transcripts for grammar, tone, and professional clarity before they are injected.
- **Cross-Platform Pasting**: Improved the reliability of automatic text pasting across macOS and Windows with intelligent focus-target capturing.
- **Dictation Service**: Implemented a new dictation engine using Edge Function WebSocket proxies for high-speed, short-form speech recognition.
 
### Local Sidecar & Offline Support:
- **Offline AI Logic**: Full integration with the Transkit Local Sidecar, enabling private, offline LLM (Llama 3), STT (Whisper), and TTS services.
- **Granular Control**: New settings to filter which local components are active and a quick-access button to manage the model cache directory.
- **System Prompts**: Local AI models now support custom system prompts for tailored assistant behavior.
 
### UI & Core Enhancements:
- **STT Lifecycle Standard**: Standardized the `finalize()` method across all transcription providers to ensure clean session termination and consistent results.
- **Protocol Normalization**: Refined how the frontend handles transcript events from various providers, ensuring a unified experience regardless of the selected service.
- **Config UI Refinement**: Improved the layout and responsiveness of the configuration windows.


## 3.2.5 (2026-04-06)

### Voice Anywhere & Global Inclusion:
- **Voice Anywhere FAB**: Introduced a global floating action button (FAB) for instant voice-to-text input. Dictate anywhere and inject text directly into any active application (Zoom, Teams, Slack, etc.).
- **Realtime Caption Overlay**: Added a dedicated caption window that displays live transcription results right above the FAB as you speak.
- **Smart Visual States**: The FAB features 5 dynamic states: Idle (swirling pulse), Listening (live amplitude bars), Processing (spinner), Injecting (success flash), and Error (red alert).
- **Customizable Aesthetics**: New configuration option for **Idle Button Color**, allowing the FAB to blend perfectly with your desktop theme.
- **Drag & Toggle**: Intelligent interaction design that distinguishes between a quick tap (toggle recording) and a long-press/drag (reposition window).

### Realtime Monitor & PTT Enhancements:
- **Push-to-Talk (PTT) Toggle**: Dedicated toolbar button in the Monitor window to quickly enable/disable PTT mode.
- **Live Service Switching**: Support for switching transcription services (e.g., Deepgram to Gladia) on-the-fly without stopping the session.
- **Modern Log Aesthetics**: Updated the Monitor log bubbles with consistent, blue-tinted visual styles for improved clarity and readability.
- **Initialization Guards**: Added start-up concurrency guards to prevent multiple simultaneous session requests, ensuring stability during rapid toggling.

### Account & Subscription Management:
- **STT Addons & Team Plans**: Enhanced the Account dashboard to support purchasing STT minute bundles and managing Team-based collaborative plans.
- **Subscription Awareness**: Added dedicated UI for tracking plan expiration dates and quotas for STT, TTS, and AI credits.
- **Secure Sign-out Flow**: New `SignOutButton` with a confirmation modal to prevent accidental logouts. Sign-out now correctly targets local session scope for better multi-account handling.

### Core & Configuration:
- **Hotkeys & Voice Input Config**: New dedicated configuration pages for global Hotkeys and specific Voice Input settings, including sensitivity and delay controls.
- **Source Area Refinement**: Improved focus handling and text injection logic to ensure cursor stability when pasting dictated text.

## 3.2.4 (2026-04-01)

### UI & UX Enhancements:
- **Header Theme Toggle**: Added a compact sun/moon switch directly in the Config window header for instant light/dark mode switching.
- **Config Window Refactor**: Increased sidebar width to **250px** for better readability and improved title/control alignment.
- **Export Transcript**: New "Export transcript" action in the Monitor window to save your session snapshots.
- **Improved i18n**: Added "Session expired" handling and refined labels for account usage.

### TTS & Narration Expansion:
- **Google Cloud TTS (Chirp3-HD)**: Integrated professional-grade TTS support with full control over **Voice**, **Speaking Rate**, and **Pitch**.
- **Enhanced Windows Narration**:
  - Full support for **VB-Cable** on Windows to route audio to Zoom, Teams, or Google Meet.
  - Added step-by-step setup hints and direct download links for VB-Cable in the settings.
  - Dynamic checklist labels that reflect the selected virtual device (`{{device}}`).

### Documentation & Credits:
- **README Restructure**: Simplified the top-level description and moved project credits (fork from Pot Desktop) to a dedicated "Credits" section, emphasizing the significant improvements and modifications made.

## 3.2.3 (2026-03-31)

### Narration & Audio Routing:
- **Narration Mode (PTT) — Now supporting macOS & Windows**: Integrated Push-To-Talk support for virtual microphone output—perfect for translating and narrating directly into Zoom, Google Meet, Teams, etc.
- **Virtual Audio Setup**: Step-by-step guide and test tone generator for routing audio via virtual drivers (e.g., BlackHole on macOS, VB-Audio on Windows).
- **Virtual Mic Checklist**: New guides for routing conference mic to Transkit's virtual output.

### AI Assistant & Context Insights:
- **Expanded AI Assistant Panel**: Added a dedicated sidebar for real-time analysis with **Smart Context Insights**:
  - **Modes**: Suggest Answer, Quick Insight, Summarize, and Follow-up.
  - **Analysis**: Automatic extraction of **Key Points**, **Next Steps**, and **Questions to Ask** from conversations.
- **Improved AI Regeneration**: Support for regenerating suggestions on the fly.
- **Language Flexible AI**: AI can now reply in both languages (Source/Target) for better cross-cultural understanding.

### Source Area & Dev Productivity:
- **Redesigned Source Area**: Refactored the core translation input component for improved performance, synchronous state recovery, and smarter focus handling.
- **Variable Name Transformer**: New shortcut (**Alt+Shift+U**) to instantly toggle selected text between `snake_case`, `kebab-case`, `camelCase`, `PascalCase`, and more.
- **Custom STT Provider**: Support for arbitrary WebSocket-based transcription services with custom connection parameters (WS URL, API Key, Delay).

### Visual & Stability Polish:
- **GIF Demonstrations**: Updated READMEs with high-quality animated guides for Clipboard Listening, Screenshot OCR, and Translation.
- **Improved Auto-save UX**: Added "Open saved file" and "Open transcripts folder" actions trực tiếp từ Monitor toolbar.
- **Cloud Infrastructure**: Deployed stable `get-cloud-credentials` edge functions for seamless Transkit Cloud session management.

## 3.2.2 (2026-03-28)

### Audio Monitor & STT Enhancements:
- **Custom Vocabulary Support**: Added support for custom vocabulary in **Deepgram** and **Gladia** to improve recognition of specialized terms.
- **Advanced Controls**: Exposed endpointing and threshold controls for **Transkit Cloud** transcription.
- **Improved Auto-save UX**: New labels and tooltips for auto-save status; added quick-open actions for saved transcript files and folders.

### UI & Core Fixes:
- **Source Area Redesign**: Refactored the translation source area with improved focus handling, state recovery, and variable name transformation.
- **Font & Style Adjustments**: Standardized source text font size to 14px and optimized configuration row spacing.
- **Stability Fixes**: Normalized boolean configuration values and improved window event synchronization.

### Documentation:
- **Visual Guides**: Added the "Realtime Audio Monitor" featured row and updated example GIFs in all README files.

## 3.2.1 (2026-03-27)

### Transkit Cloud & Account:
- **Major i18n Expansion**: Complete English and Vietnamese translations for **Transkit Cloud** account management, including plan levels (Free Trial, Starter, Pro) and detailed usage tracking for STT, TTS, and AI.
- **Built-in Cloud Providers**: Introduced **Transkit Cloud** as a zero-config provider for Translation, TTS, AI, and STT (powered by Gemini 2.5 Flash and ElevenLabs).
- **Quota Management**: Real-time tracking of transcription minutes, TTS characters, and AI requests with automatic "Quota Reached" notifications and upgrade paths.
- **Authentication Conflict Fixes**: Added automatic retry prompts and informative states for concurrent auth token requests.

### User Interface & Experience:
- **Sorting Options**: Transcripts can now be sorted "Newest at top" or "Newest at bottom" with persistent UI labels.
- **Improved Error Messaging**: Dynamic "Missing API Key" errors that guide users directly to the relevant provider settings.
- **Auto-save Status**: Clearer "Auto-save ON" indicators in the Monitor toolbar.
- **Subtitle Mode (SubMode)**: New visual documentation and guide for the minimized overlay mode.

### Distribution & Installation:
- **Official Homebrew Support**: Install via the new tap: `brew install --cask transkit`.
- **Winget Integration**: Verified and updated instructions for installing via `winget install TransKit`.
- **Provider Transparency**: Added clear credit information for Soniox, Deepgram ($200 credit), and Gladia (10h/month free).

## 3.2.0 (2026-03-25)

### Documentation & Global Support:
- **Default Multi-language User Guides**: Standardized English (`docs/user_guide.md`) as primary and Vietnamese (`docs/user_guide_vi.md`) as supplementary guides.
- **Enhanced macOS Support**: Added detailed instructions for unsigned app workarounds (`xattr -cr`) and a step-by-step guide for Screen/Audio Recording permissions.
- **Developer Options**: Added instructions for building in **Local-only mode** (`VITE_DISABLE_CLOUD=true`) to bypass Supabase/Cloud dependency.
- **Visual Aids**: Integrated high-quality UI screenshots into both READMEs and User Guides.

### Major Improvements (Refining 3.1.x):
- **New Realtime Transcription Providers**:
  - **Deepgram**: Fast STT with $200 free credit; supports built-in Google Translation.
  - **Gladia**: WebSocket live streaming with 10 free hours per month; features speaker diarization.
  - **Soniox**: Low-latency transcription for professional meetings.
- **Realtime Monitor Enhancements**:
  - **AI Suggestion & Context**: Tightly integrated LLMs (Gemini, OpenAI, Claude) to solve specialized terminology in real-time.
  - **SubMode**: Overlay subtitle mode for movies and video calls.
  - **Smart Sorting**: Toolbar options to sort transcripts newest-first or oldest-first.
  - **Placeholder Redesign**: Quick-access provider switching and direct session start.
- **Core & Performance**:
  - **Installer Optimization**: Reduced installer size by 20MB by removing heavy local detection engines.
  - **Cloud Session Tracking**: Live countdown for trial usage and account-based synchronization.
- **TTS Upgrades**: Support for Edge TTS (free/built-in), ElevenLabs, and OpenAI-compatible streaming TTS.
- **Clipboard Sync**: "Monitor Clipboard" feature to automatically translate any copied text in the background.

